Third-party components bundled in this repository
=================================================

LAME (libmp3lame) — MP3 encoding
--------------------------------
Hark's MP3 output uses libmp3lame, vendored (encode-only) under
Sources/CLame/ from LAME 3.100 (https://lame.sourceforge.io/).

LAME is licensed under the GNU Lesser General Public License (LGPL),
version 2.1. See https://www.gnu.org/licenses/old-licenses/lgpl-2.1.html
for the full license text. The vendored sources retain their original
copyright headers.

Only the encoder is included; the MP3 decoder (mpglib) and SIMD
(xmm_quantize_sub.c) sources are omitted, and a minimal Sources/CLame/config.h
replaces LAME's autoconf-generated config.h.

FlyingFox / FlyingSocks — embedded HTTP server
----------------------------------------------
The remote-control agent (`hark --remote-control`, PRD §6.10) serves its
HTTP/JSON control API using FlyingFox and FlyingSocks
(https://github.com/swhitty/FlyingFox), added as SwiftPM dependencies and
statically linked into the binary (nothing for users to install).

FlyingFox is licensed under the MIT License. Copyright (c) 2022 Simon Whitty.
See the project's LICENSE for the full text.

SwiftPM dependencies (statically linked)
----------------------------------------
The release binary statically links the following Swift packages. Each is used
under its own license; all are permissive (MIT or Apache-2.0).

  swift-argument-parser (Apache-2.0) — https://github.com/apple/swift-argument-parser
  WhisperKit / argmax-oss-swift (MIT) — https://github.com/argmaxinc/argmax-oss-swift
  FluidAudio (Apache-2.0) — https://github.com/FluidInference/FluidAudio

These pull in further permissive transitive dependencies (Apache-2.0:
swift-asn1, swift-collections, swift-crypto, swift-jinja, swift-transformers;
MIT: yyjson). The Apache-2.0 license is available at
https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0 and the MIT license at
https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT; each project retains its own LICENSE and
copyright notices.

Runtime tools (not bundled)
---------------------------
The default `whisper` engine invokes an external whisper.cpp binary
(`whisper-cli`/`whisper-server`, e.g. `brew install whisper-cpp`); it is not
bundled with or linked into Hark.
